It was the Social Democratic Chancellor Werner Faymann highly personal, this decision ends of the Council of Ministers, although the Austrian state public debt at 74.6%, much of the by the Maastricht Treaty set criterion of 60%, well below the debt levels of countries such as Italy, Greece or Spain.
